{{Orphan|date=December 2012}} {{Infobox Magazine |title = Errr-Magazine |image_file = Errr-magazine 6.png |image_size = |image_caption = ''Errr-Magazine'' #6 |editor_title = |editor = Abel Ibáñez Galván / Andrea Belmont |previous_editor = |staff_writer = |frequency = Bi-Monthly |circulation = |headquarters = |category = |company = |publisher = |firstdate = March 2009 |country = [[Mexico]] |based = [[Mexico City]] |language = Spanish |website = [http://www.errr-magazine.com www.errr-magazine.com] |issn = }}
'''''Errr-Magazine''''' is a Mexican magazine devoted to art and literature. Its first edition (labeled no. -1) was published in March 2009 and dealt with creative experience.<ref name="radio_ibero">{{cite episode|title=Anna Stephens|url=http://www.ibero909.fm/anna/|credits=Anna Stephens|network=Radio Ibero|station=XHUIA-FM|location=Mexico City|airdate=15 May 2009|minutes=0:00|series=Anna Stephens}}</ref> The magazine is published bi-monthly, and encourages artists and writers to send their work. The magazine is based in Mexico City and is distributed free.<ref>{{cite news|title=This magazine is FREE|url=http://errr-magazine.com/|accessdate=19 June 2016|work=Errr-Magazine}}</ref> Mexican author [[Jorge Volpi]] has contributed to the magazine. Originally, the magazine set topics such as memory or creative experience, as a theme for an edition. However, as of the 3rd edition, this no longer holds true.
