The '''Los Angeles Women's Music Festival''' was a 2007 [[Los Angeles]] based summer [[music festival]] that featured exclusively female solo artists and female-led bands.
==Overview== In 2007, Los Angeles based female musicians [[Gayle Day]], [[Miria (singer)]], [[Gilli Moon]] and Toni Koch, in partnership with [[Warrior Girl Music]], [[SheJay]], and [[Adventure Art Entertainment]], produced the first women's music festival in Los Angeles. Inspired by [[Lilith Fair]] and held at Woodley Park (CA), home of WorldFest (LA), Los Angeles' largest Earth Day festival, the Los Angeles Women's Music Festival was an eco-music-fest featuring over 65 bands on 5 solar-powered stages, offering vegan, vegetarian and organic refreshments, and featuring pet adoptions, and was attended by over 2500 people. The Los Angeles Women's Music Festival also donated a percentage of proceeds to Los Angeles animal rescue groups. The festival was started in 2007 as an annual festival but was on hiatus during 2008 and was scheduled to return in 2009, although the latter event never materialized. As of 2015, it is on indefinite hiatus due to financial challenges.<ref>[http://www.lawmf.com/about.html Los Angeles Women’s Music Festival official website: About] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080517125648/http://www.lawmf.com/about.html |date=2008-05-17 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.myspace.com/lawmf07 MySpace: Los Angeles Women’s Music Festival Newsletter - Vol. 1 Issue 1 - March 8, 2008]</ref><ref>[http://upcoming.yahoo.com/event/218388/ Yahoo! Upcoming Events 2007] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120718113314/http://upcoming.yahoo.com/event/218388/ |date=2012-07-18 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lawmf.com |title=Los Angeles Women's Music Festival |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2015 |website=lawmf.com |access-date=2 July 2017 }}</ref>
==Females on Fire== The official theme of the 2007 Los Angeles Women's Music Festival was ''Females on Fire'' after [http://www.warriorgirlmusic.com Warrior Girl Music]'s compilation albums by the same name. The [[Females on Fire]] CD compilations also feature female solo artists and female-led bands.<ref>[http://www.femalesonfire.com Females on Fire official website]</ref>
==Performers==
